Docs.remarks:
Equal components get all their bits set to 1;
        Unequal components gets the value set to zero.  You can compare the integer
		properties to Byte.MaxValue.

Equal components get all their bits set to 1;
	        Unequal components gets the value set to zero.  You can compare the integer
			properties to -1.

Equal components get all their bits set to 1;
        Unequal components gets the value set to zero.  You can compare the integer properties to
        -1l.

Equal components get all their bits set to 1;
        Unequal components gets the value set to zero.  You can compare the integer properties to
        UInt64.MaxValue.

Equal components get all their bits set to 1;
        Unequal components gets the value set to zero.  You can
		compare the integer properties to -1.

Equal components get all their bits set to 1;
        Unequal components gets the value set to zero.  You can
		compare the integer properties to UInt32.MaxValue.

Equal components get all their bits set to 1;
        Unequal components gets the value set to zero.  You can
 		compare the integer properties to -1.

Equal components get all their bits set to 1;
        Unequal components gets the value set to zero.  You can
		compare the integer properties to UInt16.MaxValue.
